The article is a readout of a call between President Obama and British Prime Minister Cameron regarding Afghanistan. The Prime Minister confirmed that Lieutenant General Nick Parker would act as the Commander of NATO's International Security Assistance Force mission until a new US Commander is confirmed by Congress. The President expressed his desire for General David Petraeus to be confirmed for this role as soon as possible. Prime Minister Cameron assured the President that the mission would continue without interruption and that he had confidence in the shared strategy for Afghanistan and Pakistan.